what is medical imaging?

Medical imaging is the technique and process of creating visual representations of the interior of a body
for clinical analysis and medical intervention.

Some medical imaging used in medical.

1. X-RAY
2. Magnetic resonance imaging.
3. Medical ultras
4. Endoscopy. 
5. Elastography.
6. tactile imaging.
7. Thermography.
8. Positron emission tomography (PET).
9. Single-photon emission computed tomography (SPECT)onography. 
